1. Create a DockerFile to containerize app.js
2. From a lightweight node.js alpine version
3. set a working dir
4. declare ports for exposing ports (in docker-compose.yml)
4. copy package*.json to workdir (as it's needed for the npm install command - to install dependencies)
5. copy .env.example to .env file (for use by docker-compose)
5. run commands npm install
6. declare a mount volume ? (not needed, but good for practice)
7. copy disk dir to virtual docker workdir
8. CMD directive - run node app e.g. npm start server.js etc.

9. Setup Docker-compose.yml file 
10. auto network exists; add services
	-- app.js (specify build command instead of image command)
	-- mariaDB.js (specify image command)
11. set depends_on on app.js to watch for maria_db container
11. set healthcheck for mariadb
12. Set volumes, port, environment vars using env file
13. run docker compose up
